{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e1c0f856-79cb-40d4-96f2-8220b92a51ae","content":"The `.testsettings` format is **not supported in MSTest v3**. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's how each setting maps:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout` property | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` |\n| Code Coverage data collector | `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>` |\n| `AssemblyResolution useLoadContext` | No longer needed (MSTest v3 loads in-place by default) |","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_qjSReaBY0Wx164XCy7bH8c","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_QDZD31SAw52CeJOe7BMFoU","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-d6f6beca510c495394b4b1b7545f1fca/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n                     uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n                     assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.dll\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <CodeCoverage />\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-d6f6beca510c495394b4b1b7545f1fca/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"ca2089b5-4a52-48ef-a14f-ca93e1596fca","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n\n1. A `.testsettings` file with:\n   - Test deployment config (AssemblyResolution with useLoadContext)\n   - A test timeout of 30000ms (30 seconds)\n   - A code coverage data collector\n\n2. A `.csproj` that references MSTest 3.8.0\n\nThe `.testsettings` format is a legacy format that MSTest v3 no longer supports. The modern replacement is a `.runsettings` file. Let me explain how to migrate each setting:\n\n1. **Test timeout** → In `.runsettings` under `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` or use `[Timeout]` attribute, or in `.runsettings` under `<MSTestV2><TestTimeout>`.\n\n\n2. **Code coverage data collector** → In `.runsettings` under `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>`.\n3. **Assembly resolution / deployment** → In `.runsettings` under `<MSTest><DeploymentEnabled>` or similar.\n\nNow I'm building the `.runsettings` file that will replace the old `.testsettings` configuration...\n\nWriting the RunSettings XML...\n\nActually, let me reconsider the structure for MSTest v3 — the timeout setting goes directly under `<MSTest>`, and code coverage configuration lives in the `<DataCollectionRunSettings>` section with the appropriate data collector URI and assembly reference.\n\nI should also think about how assembly resolution works in the newer version. The old `.testsettings` approach with `useLoadContext` has been replaced, and MSTest v3 handles deployment differently by default, running tests in their original location rather than copying them. I'm considering whether to reference the `.runsettings` file from the project file itself, which would be the modern best practice.\n\nFor the code coverage collector configuration...\n\nConfiguring code coverage settings...","outputTokens":1311,"requestId":"EC2E:9D49C:645C8EB:6CD5CE3:6A034B89"},"id":"715b4a99-b499-4da4-bc89-a9419a3b7371","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:47:47.478Z","parentId":"38ef749a-6336-4697-a55c-53d95cea26db"}
